<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFF8F61689B035A4FDE3FDD4" pageId="60" pageNumber="118" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFF8F61689B035A4FDE3FDD4" blockId="60.[171,1379,282,670]" pageId="60" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="B970EAFEFFF8F61689B035A4FDBFFE42" bold="true" box="[174,538,440,473]" pageId="60" pageNumber="118">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Round-eared Tube-nosed Fruit Bat is currently known from two male specimens collected more than 100 years ago from the Arfak Mountains. Virtually nothing is known about its ecology and threats.
</paragraph>
